  <span id="freeText2859094111986155060" style="display:none">While the author uses his own lexicon such as the Source and the faces of intention, the premise of this book is quite simple: thoughts become actions. <br /><br />I did struggle reading this book. Not because of the content, but because of the repetitiveness nature of the book. But, I gleaned one important thing from this book - to love oneself. By doing so, you change your thoughts and subsequent behaviors. By repeating the affirmation "I Love Me" with affirmations that support your desires, you will achieve the things you want in life. <br /><br />My recommendation for other readers of this book is to scan the table of contents and read the chapters that would be of the most assistance in your life at that given point in time.</span>
