<div id="review_3362810234" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3362810234" />
    <a title="Kushagra Singh" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34283553-kushagra-singh"><img alt="Kushagra Singh" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1623516197p2/34283553.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3362810234?book_show_action=true">Jun 03, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kushagra Singh" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kushagra Singh" href="/user/show/34283553-kushagra-singh">Kushagra Singh</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/19225583-the-power-of-intention">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3362810234" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7242851332557976058">I had this book in my wish list since the past couple of years, I think. The title, the author and the cover had attracted me towards it though somehow I didn’t purchase it. <br/><br/>I’m happy that the universe manifested this book for me at what I believe is a perfect time. <br/><br/>Dr Wayne is an inspirational spiritual teacher. He has left his mortal body, but his work continues to inspire many like me to re-connect to the power of the spirit that is the source of all. <br/><br/>Since the beginning of 2020, I have often</span>
  <span id="freeText7242851332557976058" style="display:none">I had this book in my wish list since the past couple of years, I think. The title, the author and the cover had attracted me towards it though somehow I didn’t purchase it. <br /><br />I’m happy that the universe manifested this book for me at what I believe is a perfect time. <br /><br />Dr Wayne is an inspirational spiritual teacher. He has left his mortal body, but his work continues to inspire many like me to re-connect to the power of the spirit that is the source of all. <br /><br />Since the beginning of 2020, I have often had the blessing to hear his talks and conversations with people. Every content of his reflects wisdom, clarity, the profoundness of personal experience and intention of purpose to live a spiritual life. <br /><br />I misjudged this book to be a book on the law of attraction, but, it’s not just about manifesting your desires; the book has profoundly enriching philosophy and profound wisdom to live a good life. <br /><br />I’m so mellowed and positively charged getting the company of Dr Dyer through this book and his words. I did not plan on completing the book within a few days of starting it. However, the book had me hooked onto it, and I completed it a few sittings. <br /><br />The inherent theme of the book is the cultivation of faith and active connection to what we call the source of all- spirit. The book is a motivational document to rekindle the link to that from which we’ve emerged. Once you’re able to do that, manifestation is a piece of cake :) <br /><br />Recommended. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7242851332557976058" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


